  CORE ARGUMENT: Jutten defends and critically reconstructs Habermas' colonization thesis -- the claim that reification in modern societies arises when the communicative infrastructure of the lifeworld is colonized by money and power operating according to system logic. He argues the thesis remains compelling thirty years after TCA but requires modification: Habermas' functionalist framing cannot explain what is normatively wrong with colonization from the perspective of the persons affected, because it lacks a theory of the first-person experience of reification.

